body:
If a REST resource references a path param in its method signature, and a sub resource references the same path param, then the generated openapi json has the parameter in it twice and it fails OpenAPI validation in tools like readme.com and https://validator.swagger.io/

E.g.

REST resource:
```
@Path("/{tenantId}/{paymentId}")
    public PaymentResource getPaymentResource(@PathParam("tenantId") long tenantId, @PathParam("paymentId") long paymentId) {
        return paymentResource;
    }
```
Sub resource (paymentResource):
```
    @POST
    @Path("refunds")
    public PaymentRefundResult initiateRefund(@PathParam("tenantId") long tenantId, @PathParam("paymentId") long paymentId,
            @Valid EclipsePaymentRefund refund) {
        return eclipsePaymentService.initiateRefund(tenantId, paymentId, refund);
    }
```

OpenAPI generated by Quarkus 2.12:
"/{paymentId}/refunds" : {
      "post" : {
        "tags" : [ "q) Payments" ],
        "summary" : "Refund a portion or entire payment amount",
        "description" : "Processes a refund. The amount cannot exceed the original amount",
        "parameters" : [ {
          "name" : "paymentId",
          "in" : "path",
          "required" : true,
          "schema" : {
            "format" : "int64",
            "type" : "integer"
          }
        }, {
          "name" : "tenantId",
          "in" : "path",
          "required" : true,
          "schema" : {
            "format" : "int64",
            "type" : "integer"
          }
        } ],
        "requestBody" : {
          "content" : {
            "application/json" : {
              "schema" : {
                "$ref" : "#/components/schemas/EclipsePaymentRefund"
              }
            }
          }
        },
        "responses" : {
          "200" : {
            "description" : "OK",
            "content" : {
              "application/json" : {
                "schema" : {
                  "$ref" : "#/components/schemas/PaymentRefundResult"
                }
              }
            }
          }
        },
        "security" : [ {
          "JWTBearerAuthorisation" : [ ]
        } ]
      },
      "parameters" : [ {
        "name" : "tenantId",
        "in" : "path",
        "required" : true,
        "schema" : {
          "format" : "int64",
          "type" : "integer"
        }
      }, {
        "name" : "paymentId",
        "in" : "path",
        "required" : true,
        "schema" : {
          "format" : "int64",
          "type" : "integer"
        }
      }, **{
        "name" : "tenantId",
        "in" : "path",
        "required" : true,
        "schema" : {
          "format" : "int64",
          "type" : "integer"
        }**
      } ]
    }

Quarkus 2.11.3 does not duplicate the tenantId param
